Package de.oth.hsp.common.dat

Incorporates all classes handling .dat files.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractConstraint
    Used to describe relationships between one/multiple DatEntry objects and one dependent DatEntry.
    AbstractDatFile
    Children of this class represent certain kinds .dat files.

    When implementing a new model class make sure to call AbstractDatFile.initialize() at the end of its constructor.
    DatEntry<T extends DatContent>
    Represents entries in a .dat file.
    DatFileParser
    Handles the parsing of .dat files.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    NumericalType
    Defines the numerical type of all values stored in an entry.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ConstraintException
    Used to indicate an error when validating a AbstractConstraint relation.
